d Kingdom","Barlow, Derbyshire, England":"Barlow, Derbyshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Barlow","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from any of several places called Barlow, especially those in Lancashire and Yorkshire. The former is named with Old English <i>bere</i> ‘barley’ + <i>hlāw</i> ‘hill’; the latter probably has as its first element the derived adjective <i>beren</i> or the compound <i>bere-ærn</i> ‘barn’. There is also a place of this name in Derbyshire, named with Old English <i>bār</i> ‘boar’ or <i>bere</i> ‘barley’ + <i>lēah</i> ‘woodland clearing’, and one in Shropshire, which is from <i>bere</i> ‘barley’ + <i>lēah</i>."],"variants":[{"name":"Barlowe","meanings":["English: variant of   Barlow  ."]}]},{"name":"Robert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Robert Barlow was born in 1425, in Barlow, Derbyshire, England, United Kingdom. He had at least 1 daughter with Elena Cockayne. He died in 1530, in England, United Kingdom, at the age of 105."},"et":{"Abt 1425–1530":"1425–1530","1430–Female":"1430–Surnud","1446–1480":"1446–1480","1425–1530":"1425–1530","1425":"1425","1446":"1446","Abt 1480":"umbes 1480","1530":"1530","1430":"1430","Abt 1425":"1425","1480":"1480","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Barlow, Derbyshire, England":"Barlow, Derbyshire, England"},"fi":{"Abt 1425–1530":"1425–1530","1430–Female":"1430–Kuollut","1446–1480":"1446–1480","1425–1530":"1425–1530","1425":"1425","1446":"1446","Abt 1480":"noin 1480","1530":"1530","1430":"1430","Abt 1425":"1425","1480":"1480","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Barlow, Derbyshire, England":"Barlow, Derbyshire, England"},"fr":{"Abt 1425–1530":"1425–1530","1430–Female":"1430–Décédée","1446–1480":"1446–1480","1425–1530":"1425–1530","1425":"1425","1446":"1446","Abt 1480":"environ 1480","1530":"1530","1430":"1430","Abt 1425":"1425","1480":"1480","England":"Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Barlow, Derbyshire, England":"Barlow, Derbyshire, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Robert Barlow est né en 1425, à Barlow, Derbyshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Il a eu au moins 1 fille avec Elena Cockayne. Il est décédé en 1530, à Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, à l’âge de 105 ans."},"de":{"Abt 1425–1530":"1425–1530","1430–Female":"1430–Verstorben","1446–1480":"1446–1480","1425–1530":"1425–1530","1425":"1425","1446":"1446","Abt 1480":"um 1480","1530":"1530","1430":"1430","Abt 1425":"1425","1480":"1480","England":"England, United Kingdom","Barlow, Derbyshire, England":"Barlow, Derbyshire, England","lifeSummary":"Robert Barlow wurde 1425 in Barlow, Derbyshire, England, United Kingdom geboren. Er hatte mit Elena Cockayne mindestens 1 Tochter. Er starb 1530 im Alter von 105 Jahren in England, United Kingdom."},"ht":{"Abt 1425–1530":"1425–1530","1430–Female":"1430–Desede","1446–1480":"1446–1480","1425–1530":"1425–1530","1425":"1425","1446":"1446","Abt 1480":"about 1480","1530":"1530","1430":"1430","Abt 1425":"1425","1480":"1480","England":"Angle